SVG Tag : 
	The <svg> tag is mainly used to create scalable graphics such as icons, logos, charts,
	shapes, animations, diagrams, and interactive visuals that remain sharp on all screen 
	sizes unlike normal images.
	
Common svg elements : 
| Element     | Purpose                      |
| ----------- | ---------------------------- |
|  <circle>   | Draws a circle               |
|  <rect>     | Draws a rectangle            |
|  <line>     | Draws a line                 |
|  <polygon>  | Draws shapes with many sides |
|  <path>     | Draws complex shapes         |
|  <text>     | Displays text                |


Automating SVG elements in Selenium is slightly different from normal HTML elements because 
SVG elements do not behave like standard DOM tags.

Normal locators like //svg or //circle often do not work directly.

local-name() in XPath : //*[local-name()='svg']
						//*[local-name()='svg']//*[local-name()='path']
